.TH ADSMT\-LSP 1 "2026-06-01" "adsmt 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
adsmt\-lsp \- Language Server Protocol server for SMT\-LIB v2 and lu\-kb
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B adsmt\-lsp
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B adsmt\-lsp
is a tower\-lsp based Language Server Protocol server for the
.B adsmt
project. It activates on
.B .smt2
(SMT\-LIB v2) and
.B .kb
(lu\-kb) files, communicating with editors via stdin/stdout in the
standard LSP framing.

Six LSP capabilities are exposed (v1.0):
.IP "\(bu" 2
.B textDocument/publishDiagnostics
\(em parser + audit diagnostics
.IP "\(bu" 2
.B textDocument/definition
\(em within\-document symbol resolution
.IP "\(bu" 2
.B textDocument/hover
\(em BV literal annotation, declaration preview, last verdict for
.B (check\-sat)
cursors
.IP "\(bu" 2
.B textDocument/completion
\(em 39 static items (SMT\-LIB commands, theory names,
classical\-axiom families, lu\-kb keywords)
.IP "\(bu" 2
.B workspace/symbol
\(em case\-insensitive substring search across open documents
.IP "\(bu" 2
.B textDocument/codeAction
\(em kb\-file migration placeholder, abductive\-accept code actions

.SH OPTIONS
The server reads its configuration from the LSP client's
.B initializationOptions
block. Recognised keys:
.TP
.B abductiveTier
0\(en4. Default 4.
.TP
.B triggerMode
.BR miller " | " free .
Default
.BR miller .
.TP
.B classicalAxioms
Array of strings (e.g.
.BR ["lem"] ).
.TP
.B auditFormat
.BR json " | " text .
Default
.BR json .

No command\-line options apart from
.BR \-h " / " \-\-help
(usage summary) and
.BR \-V " / " \-\-version .

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ADSMT_LOG
Log level: one of
.BR error ", " warn ", " info ", " debug ", " trace .
Logs go to standard error so they don't corrupt the LSP message
stream on standard output.

.SH FILES
The server has no persistent state files of its own. Audit
diagnostics, when configured for JSON output, are pushed through
the LSP
.B audit/diagnostics
notification channel; editors may persist them at their discretion.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lu\-smt (1),
.BR lu\-kb (5)
.SH AUTHOR
NEWSNIPER.
